snippet.textDisplay:
You big California baby, that hill was NOTHING.
Coming from someone that grew up in Maine but lives in California now.

My friend when I grew up in Maine had a massive pile of dirt in her backyard for a couple years, I'm talking like almost 2 stories, and when it snowed we went sledding down that monster, frequently on one of the little foam ones you can barely hang on to. We ended up making this bump from going over it so many times and combined with some ice, at first it just hurt our asses to go over, then we started getting air off it, and it got to the point that we were nearly flying over the neighbor's fence.


Or that time my family went to this super legit snow tubing place (like full on ski lift to get you up the hill), at the bottom of the intense hills was a giant bank to keep people from going over it into the parking lot. My dad hit it fast enough that he got air going over the bank.
